Mai Nhat Duy is a Junior AI/NLP Engineer with 0 years of commercial experience. Their core expertise lies in Artificial Intelligence (AI) and Natural Language Processing (NLP) using architectures such as Large Language Models (LLM) and Small Language Models (SLM), with a strong focus on techniques like Model Training, Fine-tuning, and Chatbot Development. Through academic projects, they have demonstrated the ability to apply these concepts to real-world problems, including the development of a Lightweight LLM for Vietnamese Medical Texts, where they utilized Marker, Datatrove, and Unsloth to create an efficient SLM capable of understanding and accurately answering Vietnamese medical questions, and a Chatbot Integrated with Agnetic RAG, leveraging LangGraph, LangChain, Elasticsearch, and Vector Database to enhance flexibility and accuracy in information retrieval.

Technically, Mai Nhat Duy is proficient in programming languages such as Python and Java, and has hands-on experience with frameworks and libraries including PyTorch, Transformer, DeepSpeed, Hugging Face, LangGraph, and LangChain. They are also familiar with databases like Elasticsearch, Vector Database, and SQL Database, and have worked with tools and platforms such as Marker and Datatrove. Their domain knowledge spans areas like Information Retrieval, Indexing, and Generation, with a particular emphasis on NLP applications. With a strong foundation in Computer Science, currently pursuing a Bachelor's degree at Ton Duc Thang University, Mai Nhat Duy possesses a solid educational background that complements their technical skills, making them a promising junior engineer in the field of AI and NLP.